Business Brief -- Rogers Corp.:
   Firm Expects to Post Loss
   Totaling $2.3 Million for '91
"The recession has severely affected sales, particularly
in the computer disk drive and automotive markets," Norman L.
Greenman, the company's president, said in a release. He said
that Rogers remains financially strong and that the
write-offs and cost-cutting will "accelerate the return to
profitability when the economy improves."